[[Category:Medical jurisprudence]]


{{Greece-bio-stub}}

'''Shearer West''' is a British-American [[Art history|art-historian]], academic and university administrator. She is currently the Vice-Chancellor of the [[University of Nottingham]] since October 2017 and formerly deputy [[vice-chancellor]] of the [[University of Sheffield]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://nottingham.ac.uk/news/pressreleases/2017/may/new-vice-chancellor-for-nottingham.aspx |title=New Vice-Chancellor for Nottingham |last=Cass |first=Liz |year=2017 |publisher=University of Nottingham |format=Press release}}</ref>

==Biography and career==
West holds an undergraduate degree in art history and English from the [[College of William & Mary]], in Virginia, and a PhD in art history from the [[University of St Andrews]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Shearer West named as next Nottingham v-c|url=https://www.timeshighereducation.com/news/shearer-west-named-next-nottingham-v-c|publisher=Times Higher Education|accessdate=22 May 2017}}</ref>

She was previously head of the [[Humanities Division, University of Oxford|Humanities Division]] at the [[University of Oxford]], director of research at the [[Arts and Humanities Research Council]], and head of the School of Historical Studies at the [[University of Birmingham]].<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=https://www.sheffield.ac.uk/news/nr/university-deputy-vice-chancellor-professor-shearer-west-1.451781 |title=University of Sheffield announces the appointment of new Deputy Vice-Chancellor - News releases - News - The University of Sheffield |publisher=University of Sheffield |date=2015-03-25 |accessdate=2015-10-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.alumni.ox.ac.uk/content/professor-shearer-west |title=Oxford Alumni / Professor Shearer West |publisher=[[University of Oxford]] |date= |accessdate=2015-10-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lfhe.ac.uk/en/programmes-events/you/aurora/resources/aurora-speakers/professor-shearer-west.cfm |title=Professor Shearer West |publisher=[[Leadership Foundation for Higher Education]] |date= |accessdate=2015-10-16}} {{dead link|date=October 2016}}</ref>

==Selected publications==
*''The Image of the Actor: Verbal and Visual Representation in the Age of Garrick and Kemble'', Palgrave MacMillan, 1991. {{ISBN|0312057385}}
*''Fin De Siecle: Art and society in an age of uncertainty'', The Overlook Press, 1994.
*''The visual arts in Germany 1897-1940: Utopia and Despair'', [[Rutgers University Press]], 2001. {{ISBN|0813529115}}
*''Portraiture'', [[Oxford University Press]], Oxford, 2004. ([[Oxford History of Art]])

